message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Togo, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you have the time, walking can be a good option. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a faster and more convenient option. It will take you around 5-10 minutes to reach the grocery store.

3. Public Transportation: Depending on the availability in your area, you can check for local buses or shared taxis (known as "zémidjans" or "woro-woros") that can take you to the grocery store. Ask locals or at a nearby bus stop for information on the best route.

4. Private Transportation: If you have access to a car or can hire a taxi, this can be the most convenient option. It will allow you to reach the grocery store quickly and comfortably.

Consider the factors such as weather, time, cost, and personal preference to choose the most suitable mode of transportation for your trip to the grocery store.
